com.inepex.hyperconnector.annotations
Enum TimestampAssignmentTypes

java.lang.Object

java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TimestampAssignmentTypes>
public enum TimestampAssignmentTypes
extends java.lang.Enum<TimestampAssignmentTypes>

Specifies how the value of the timestamp in a HyperEntity can be assigned upon insertion. Applies to the HyperEntity field annotated with Timestamp.

Author:
Gabor Dicso

Enum Constant Detail

AUTO_HYPERCONNECTOR

public static final TimestampAssignmentTypes AUTO_HYPERCONNECTOR
Timestamp will indicate when the HyperEntity was inserted. Timestamp previously set in the HyperEntity will be discarded upon insertion. Timestamp will be assigned by HyperConnector. The timestamp assigned to the HyperEntity by HyperConnector will be set in the given HyperEntity instance upon insertion.

AUTO_HYPERTABLE

public static final TimestampAssignmentTypes AUTO_HYPERTABLE

Suitable for HyperEntity types with exactly one Hypertable cell per HyperEntity. For HyperEntity types with more than one Hypertable cell, AUTO_HYPERTABLE will be treated as AUTO_HYPERCONNECTOR.

Timestamp will be assigned automatically by Hypertable. Note: the timestamp assigned to the HyperEntity by Hypertable will NOT be set in the given HyperEntity instance upon insertion.

MANUAL

public static final TimestampAssignmentTypes MANUAL
The HyperEntity will be inserted with the timestamp that has been assigned to the annotated HyperEntity field before insertion.

FIXED

public static final TimestampAssignmentTypes FIXED
The HyperEntity will be inserted with the fixed timestamp specified in the Timestamp annotation.
